critique: This document is an executive order that designates the European Space Research Organization (ESRO) as a public international organization entitled to enjoy those privileges, exemptions, and immunities provided for by the International Organizations Immunities Act. It also supersedes two previous executive orders. There is no direct indication of ideological tilt, immigration approach, executive power expansion, federalism implications, national security vs. civil liberties concerns, economic regulation, or social inclusion considerations. Therefore, most axes should be scored as neutral.
